<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4496853>
    dc:description "FIGURE 20. Phyllodoce longipes. A, anterior end, dorso-lateral view; B and C, detail of prostomium; C, prostomium showing nuchal papilla with white arrow; D, proboscis in lateral view. Abbreviations: Np, nuchal papilla. Scale bars: A, 1.0 mm; B–C, 0.1 mm; D, 0.01 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4496853/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4496855>
    dc:description "FIGURE 21. Phyllodoce longipes. Anterior view of parapodia.A, parapodium 10; B, parapodium 27; C, parapodium 52. Dorsal cirri with distal filaments (black arrow). D–E, compound spinigerous chaetae; F, pygidium and anal cirri, ventral view. Scale bars: A, 0.05 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm, D, 0.02 mm; E, 0.004 mm; F, 0.05 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4496855/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

